I am positive,
but I was infected in 1985.

01:14:40.560 --> 01:14:43.399
You mean you were diagnosed
in 1985?

01:14:43.400 --> 01:14:45.079
Yes.

01:14:45.080 --> 01:14:48.080
Really, there's no reason
to...

01:14:48.560 --> 01:14:50.239
1981?

01:14:50.240 --> 01:14:53.240
Mr Conigrave, you're one
ofthe lastto be contacted.

01:14:54.440 --> 01:14:57.440
The otherdonors
are all clear.

01:15:00.280 --> 01:15:03.280
Not this week, Tim.

01:15:03.320 --> 01:15:04.959
You read it?

01:15:04.960 --> 01:15:07.559
Wash your hands.
I need some help.

01:15:07.560 --> 01:15:10.359
I'm flat-out with relatives
arriving from everywhere

01:15:10.360 --> 01:15:12.799
and your father wants
his pre-wedding drinks.

01:15:12.800 --> 01:15:15.800
Al fresco is just not me.

01:15:20.520 --> 01:15:23.520
Now, can you see how to slice
and twist the salmon,

01:15:23.880 --> 01:15:26.880
just like the picture?

01:15:29.320 --> 01:15:31.639
TIM: I've been doing some
volunteering.

01:15:31.640 --> 01:15:34.439
Well, I get paid for it now.

01:15:34.440 --> 01:15:37.440
It's social work...
for the AIDS Council.

01:15:38.080 --> 01:15:41.080
Tell me I've nothing
to worry about.

01:15:52.920 --> 01:15:54.799
What a waste.

01:15:54.800 --> 01:15:57.759
All that talent.

01:15:57.760 --> 01:15:59.319
I'm not dead yet.

01:15:59.320 --> 01:16:01.399
I just don't understand
how you've got it!

01:16:01.400 --> 01:16:04.400
I mean,
it's just you and John.

01:16:05.400 --> 01:16:08.400
- We've both got it.
- Oh, God.

01:16:09.880 --> 01:16:12.880
That beautiful boy.

01:16:13.280 --> 01:16:16.280
Is it from a donation? Is that
why the Red Cross are writing?

01:16:17.360 --> 01:16:19.839
Would you prefer it that way?

01:16:19.840 --> 01:16:22.840
Did I say that?
I didn't say that.

01:16:23.840 --> 01:16:26.840
I prefer none of it,
thank you!

01:16:31.680 --> 01:16:34.680
After the wedding,
after all ofthis,

01:16:34.880 --> 01:16:37.079
I think we should tell Dad.

01:16:37.080 --> 01:16:40.080
I'm making a mess!
Look at this!

01:16:45.320 --> 01:16:48.320
This letter,
it's changed things.

01:16:50.960 --> 01:16:53.960
It says I could have been
infected... since university.

01:16:59.920 --> 01:17:02.920
John and I, we always
assumed he was first.

01:17:03.480 --> 01:17:06.480
I think I was comfortable
with that.

01:17:09.160 --> 01:17:12.160
Now it's...

01:17:12.880 --> 01:17:15.880
Mum, it's like I've killed
the man that I love!

01:17:20.280 --> 01:17:23.280
FATHER: Now, what's all this
slacking off in the kitchen?

01:17:29.440 --> 01:17:32.440
(Indistinct speech)

01:17:33.200 --> 01:17:36.200
TIM: How did it go?

01:17:36.560 --> 01:17:39.560
Mum just kept blowing
her nose.

01:17:40.600 --> 01:17:43.600
Dad wanted to talk
about my business insurance.

01:17:44.480 --> 01:17:46.119
They wanted to fall apart
alone.

01:17:46.120 --> 01:17:49.120
MAN: Drink, gentlemen?
- I can't.

01:17:51.400 --> 01:17:54.400
I suppose your parents
assume I infected you.

01:17:55.800 --> 01:17:58.800
No. Why would
you even say that?

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:05.639
I told my parents.

01:18:05.640 --> 01:18:08.640
Now?

01:18:08.760 --> 01:18:10.559
- Why?!
- Because I...

01:18:10.560 --> 01:18:12.559
How could you be so selfish?!

01:18:12.560 --> 01:18:14.119
You are gorgeous.

01:18:14.120 --> 01:18:17.120
Timothy's Aunty Gae told me
about the eyelashes.

01:18:17.520 --> 01:18:19.599
- They're false.
(Aunts laugh)

01:18:19.600 --> 01:18:22.600
We loved your dog food
commercial, Timothy.

01:18:23.400 --> 01:18:25.759
Thanks.
I'm doing social work now.

01:18:25.760 --> 01:18:28.760
- And writing another play.
- He's my PR man.

01:18:29.000 --> 01:18:31.639
Hey, do you reckon you could
introduce me to Mel Gibson?

01:18:31.640 --> 01:18:33.519
(Laughter)

01:18:33.520 --> 01:18:35.639
I work for the AIDS Council.
I'm on the hotline

01:18:35.640 --> 01:18:37.599
and the van that goes
up and down the Wall.

01:18:37.600 --> 01:18:40.079
That's where male sex workers
find their clients,

01:18:40.080 --> 01:18:41.839
and we empower them
to have safe sex

01:18:41.840 --> 01:18:43.399
and have someone to talk to.

01:18:43.400 --> 01:18:45.359
I find it really rewarding.

01:18:45.360 --> 01:18:47.079
That's nice for you, dear.

01:18:47.080 --> 01:18:50.080
John, I'm stealing you.

01:18:57.680 --> 01:19:00.680
Come on, son.
Let's show 'em how it's done.

01:19:00.760 --> 01:19:01.879
No.

01:19:01.880 --> 01:19:04.880
- Come on.
- No.

01:19:19.200 --> 01:19:21.959
- Who's leading?
BOTH: I am.

01:19:21.960 --> 01:19:24.919
* I hate to say it

01:19:24.920 --> 01:19:27.920
* But you have a right
to be free

01:19:34.040 --> 01:19:37.040
* I know it's the way
it should be

01:19:41.480 --> 01:19:44.480
* But I'm too far... *

01:19:47.200 --> 01:19:50.200
Hey! This old bloke's been
asking about you all night.

01:19:54.760 --> 01:19:57.760
Here you are, Timothy.

01:19:59.320 --> 01:20:02.320
* I love you so much
for so long... *

01:20:04.920 --> 01:20:07.920
NICHOLAS: (Laughs)
Oh, come on, Aunty Gae.

01:20:09.640 --> 01:20:12.640
Hey, Tim. Nice one, brother.

01:20:24.520 --> 01:20:27.520
You alright?

01:20:43.720 --> 01:20:45.479
I'm here, John.

01:20:45.480 --> 01:20:47.519
(Indistinctly)
My lung has popped...

01:20:47.520 --> 01:20:50.039
MAN: Try not to talk, John.
We don't want a coughing fit.

01:20:50.040 --> 01:20:52.399
Was it the chemo?

01:20:52.400 --> 01:20:55.119
More likely a burst PCP cyst.

01:20:55.120 --> 01:20:58.120
You're his boyfriend?
You're staying?

01:21:03.080 --> 01:21:04.799
Now, how's that local?

01:21:04.800 --> 01:21:07.800
JOHN: OK.

01:21:10.840 --> 01:21:13.840
I'm about to cut now, John.

01:21:28.240 --> 01:21:30.159
Right, this is going
to hurt a bit, John.

01:21:30.160 --> 01:21:33.160
(John breathes heavily)

01:21:55.560 --> 01:21:57.999
That's it, bubbling away.

01:21:58.000 --> 01:22:01.000
When the bubbles stop,
we know it's healed.

01:22:02.440 --> 01:22:05.440
(Pop music plays on stereo)

01:22:15.720 --> 01:22:18.720
(Coughing and wheezing)

01:22:22.640 --> 01:22:25.640
(CD skips)

01:22:29.880 --> 01:22:32.880
(Coughing)

01:22:40.600 --> 01:22:43.600
(Coughing continues)

01:22:48.440 --> 01:22:51.440
(Coughing continues)

01:22:53.120 --> 01:22:56.120
JOHN: Tim!

01:22:58.560 --> 01:23:01.239
MAN: Nearly there.

01:23:01.240 --> 01:23:04.159
(Wheezes)

01:23:04.160 --> 01:23:07.160
MAN: Good, good.

01:23:09.040 --> 01:23:10.759
Just a little bit more.

01:23:10.760 --> 01:23:13.479
(John whimpers)

01:23:13.480 --> 01:23:16.480
And done.

01:23:28.960 --> 01:23:30.999
He'll be in for a few days,
at least.

01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:32.879
- You have some rest.
TIM: I'm fine.

01:23:32.880 --> 01:23:35.880
It's seeing him in pain
I can't bear.

01:23:41.960 --> 01:23:44.039
He'll need his boyfriend
healthy.

01:23:44.040 --> 01:23:45.599
Ifthe lung doesn't stick,

01:23:45.600 --> 01:23:47.199
it's going to
need to be surgery,

01:23:47.200 --> 01:23:48.999
but only when
he's strong enough.

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:52.000
He'll need you.

01:24:24.520 --> 01:24:27.520
Our freezer is chockers.

01:24:27.720 --> 01:24:30.720
Penny Cook
has made you minestrone.

01:24:31.920 --> 01:24:34.920
Morna has made you minestrone.

01:24:37.480 --> 01:24:40.480
Someone has made you...
I'm not sure what that is.

01:24:45.560 --> 01:24:48.560
JOHN: Why'd you bring those?

01:24:53.760 --> 01:24:55.919
Penny's comes
with a little pesto

01:24:55.920 --> 01:24:58.920
in a separate container, so...

01:25:00.360 --> 01:25:03.360
.. let's go with that.

01:25:05.960 --> 01:25:07.559
I'm sorry.

01:25:07.560 --> 01:25:09.519
Snotty tissue got eaten

01:25:09.520 --> 01:25:12.520
by the Simpson fully
automatic.

01:25:13.640 --> 01:25:16.640
Didn't you check?

01:25:17.960 --> 01:25:20.960
Can't you do anything right?

01:25:21.040 --> 01:25:24.040
(High-pitched ringing)

01:25:44.680 --> 01:25:47.680
I'm sorry.

01:25:54.480 --> 01:25:56.399
I think I forgot the pesto.

01:25:56.400 --> 01:25:59.400
(High-pitched ringing
continues)

01:26:17.400 --> 01:26:20.400
(Alarm beeps)

01:26:22.600 --> 01:26:24.319
TIM: Will I still be able
to write?

01:26:24.320 --> 01:26:25.919
MAN: Shall we look
at your scan?

01:26:25.920 --> 01:26:28.519
TIM: I've been looking at it.
Toxoplasmosis, isn't it?

01:26:28.520 --> 01:26:30.639
- Yes, it is.
- I did a theatre thing once.

01:26:30.640 --> 01:26:32.519
Transmits via cats.
I wrote this thing.

01:26:32.520 --> 01:26:33.879
I knew I'd get it eventually.

01:26:33.880 --> 01:26:36.759
I'm thinking of getting people
together, starting something.

01:26:36.760 --> 01:26:39.319
I'm feeling very creative and
I don't want to waste that,

01:26:39.320 --> 01:26:40.879
if I'm gonna have
brain damage.

01:26:40.880 --> 01:26:43.559
- Lesions don't eat the brain.
- Which is a terrific phrase!

01:26:43.560 --> 01:26:45.119
But they do put
pressure on it.

01:26:45.120 --> 01:26:46.959
You're feeling up -
creative, you say?

01:26:46.960 --> 01:26:49.199
What about dementia,
memory loss? Sorry, go on.

01:26:49.200 --> 01:26:50.759
We'll learn more
as we treat it.

01:26:50.760 --> 01:26:52.319
I'm convinced it will happen.

01:26:52.320 --> 01:26:54.439
I'm thinking about getting
people together.

01:26:54.440 --> 01:26:55.759
You said that.

01:26:55.760 --> 01:26:58.239
I'm having ideas
and I could start something.

01:26:58.240 --> 01:27:00.759
- Tim? I think you're manic.
- Do you?

01:27:00.760 --> 01:27:02.439
Yes - the cells in your brain

01:27:02.440 --> 01:27:05.440
have become sensitive
to certain neurotransmitters.

01:27:05.760 --> 01:27:08.479
- I'm prescribing Haloperidol.
- No, I'm good. We're good.

01:27:08.480 --> 01:27:10.559
John's in here
and he's being looked after.

01:27:10.560 --> 01:27:12.639
I think we'll have to
admit you.

01:27:12.640 --> 01:27:14.559
I don't want you spending
all your money

01:27:14.560 --> 01:27:16.279
or thinking that you're Jesus.

01:27:16.280 --> 01:27:18.719
What happens to my soul
if I go mad?

01:27:18.720 --> 01:27:21.720
Does it stay trapped inside
or is it floating free?

01:28:18.640 --> 01:28:21.640
MAN: I don't want to be here!
I don't want to be here!

01:28:21.920 --> 01:28:24.920
- Get me out of...
(Voices murmur indistinctly)

01:28:35.040 --> 01:28:38.040
I don't want to be here!
Take me home!

01:28:47.240 --> 01:28:50.240
You alright there, darling?

01:28:57.560 --> 01:29:00.239
(Laughter)

01:29:00.240 --> 01:29:03.240
TIM: OK.

01:29:19.760 --> 01:29:22.760
(Tim laughs)
OK, one from the side.

01:29:24.040 --> 01:29:27.040
(Camera clicks)

01:29:30.880 --> 01:29:33.880
Are you making fun of me?

01:29:34.160 --> 01:29:37.160
I'm doing it
because you look so beautiful.

01:29:54.800 --> 01:29:57.800
- Hello, son.
- Hmm?

01:29:59.280 --> 01:30:00.839
Hi.

01:30:00.840 --> 01:30:03.840
We're just... in a good mood.
Had some good news.

01:30:05.960 --> 01:30:08.079
Would you like a chair, Bob?

01:30:08.080 --> 01:30:09.959
From the flat.

01:30:09.960 --> 01:30:12.960
Bills and stuff, eh?
Thank you.

01:30:15.400 --> 01:30:17.239
So, what are the doctors
saying, John?

01:30:17.240 --> 01:30:20.240
TIM: He's not allowed to talk.
Er, the lung again.

01:30:21.320 --> 01:30:23.599
- But we've had...
- Good news, Dad.

01:30:23.600 --> 01:30:26.600
TIM: He's not
supposed to talk.

01:30:27.040 --> 01:30:30.040
He's had some good news.
John's in remission.

01:30:30.440 --> 01:30:31.959
When he's strong enough,

01:30:31.960 --> 01:30:34.759
he'll go into surgery,
and they'll open him up,

01:30:34.760 --> 01:30:37.760
and see the snips and snails
and puppy dog tails

01:30:37.920 --> 01:30:39.479
and sew up the lung.

01:30:39.480 --> 01:30:42.480
Can you believe it? Remission!

01:30:42.560 --> 01:30:45.560
You've worked hard for it,
son.

01:30:50.320 --> 01:30:53.320
TIM: They're saying we can
probably go home

01:30:53.480 --> 01:30:55.039
in the meantime.

01:30:55.040 --> 01:30:58.040
What have you done
to his hair?

01:30:59.520 --> 01:31:01.079
It was getting ratty.

01:31:01.080 --> 01:31:03.359
(Tell him about Christmas.)

01:31:03.360 --> 01:31:06.239
- Beg your pardon?
- (Put your hearing aid in.)

01:31:06.240 --> 01:31:09.240
- 'Put your hearing aid in. '
- I don't like wearing it.

01:31:10.520 --> 01:31:13.119
John's talking about going
home for Christmas.

01:31:13.120 --> 01:31:14.919
They can't operate
until January.

01:31:14.920 --> 01:31:17.920
BOB: Your mum'll like that.
We'll fly you back down, John.

01:31:18.320 --> 01:31:19.919
He's had a pneumothorax.

01:31:19.920 --> 01:31:22.920
The airlines won't let him
fly, but I'll drive him down.

